SANTIAGO DECLARED IN STATE OF EMERGENCY
THE CHILEAN GOVERNMENT HAS DECLARED A STATE OF EMERGENCY IN SANTIAGO PROVINCE FOLLOWING A CONFUSED INCIDENT INVOLVING ARMY COMMANDER- IN- CHIEF PRATS.
AFTER WHAT WAS EITHER AN ATTEMPT AGAINST PRATS' LIFE OR AN ASSAULT ON A LADY DRIVER BY PRATS, THE GENERAL TENDERED HIS RESIGNATION, WHICH ALLENDE REFUSED.
IT WAS ALSO REPORTED THAT A COUP ATTEMPT HAD BEEN FRUSTRATED WITH THE ARREST OF AN UNDISCLOSED NUMBER OF MILITARY AND CIVILIAN PLOTTERS.
( CONFIDENTIAL) SANTIAGO 2813 AND 2829, USDAO/ SANTIAGO 281605 Z JUN, 6/28. 2.

FEDAYEEN OPPOSE PALESTINIAN STATE PROPOSAL EMBASSY BEIRUT REPORTS THAT THE IDEA OF A PALESTINIAN STATE ADVANCED BY EGYPT AND TUNISIA IS DRAWING IN- CREASING OPPOSITION FROM ALL FEDAYEEN ORGANIZATIONS.
OUR EMBASSY COMMENTS THAT MORE REASONABLE AND MODERATE FEDAYEEN LEADERS WERE APPARENTLY IN TACIT AGREEMENT WITH THE IDEA, BUT EXTREMISTS HAVE FORCED THEM TO COME OUT AGAINST IT.
( LIMITED OFFICIAL USE)
JAPANESE WORRIED ABOUT SOYBEANS
THE JAPANESE FOREIGN OFFICE HAS EXPRESSED TO EMBASSY TOKYO ITS CONCERN OVER THE IMPLICATIONS OF THE US AGRICULTURAL EXPORT EMBARGO.

THE JAPANESE INTEND TO RAISE THE QUESTION OF US RELIABILITY AS AN AGRICULTURAL SUPPLIER AT THE JULY 16-17 MINISTERIAL MEETING, AND OUR EMBASSY RECORDS INCREASING TALK IN JAPAN OF THE NEED TO DIVERSIFY AGRICULTURAL SUPPLY SOURCES AS WELL AS INCREASE SELF- SUFFICIENCY.
( CONFIDENTIAL) TOKYO 8165, 6/28. 4.
INDOCHINA ACTIVITY CAMBODIA--
THE MILITARY SITUATION ON ROUTE 6, APPROXI- MATELY 25 MILES NORTH OF PHNOM PENH, HAS DETERIORATED SHARPLY.
REINFORCEMENTS ARE BEING SENT TO THE AREA.
THE SITUATION IS COMPLICATED BY LOW QUALITY FANK TROOPS AND LEADERSHIP IN THIS AREA.
LITTLE CHANGE HAS BEEN REPORTED FROM OTHER AREAS.
( SECRET) CAMBODIAN DAMSREP, 6/29.

THE REQUIREMENT FOR MONTHLY ECONOMIC TRENDS REPORTING, INCLUDING EXTENSIVE STATISTICAL DATA, FROM THE SMALLER OECD COUNTRIES.
THE EMBASSY BELIEVES A REPORT OF THIS TYPE WILL SERVE A USEFUL PURPOSE, BUT WOULD LIKE SOME CLARIFICATION CONCERNING THE STATISTICAL INPUT.
(A) ARE THE EXTENSIVE STATISTICS OUTLINED IN MR.
GOODMAN'S MEMORANDUM TO POSTS IN NORTHERN EUROPE NEEDED FOR NEW ZEALAND AS WELL?
WE NOTE IN THIS REGARD THAT REF.
A WAS NOT CLEARED IN EITHER EUR/RPE OR IN THE EA BUREAU (EA/ANZ OR EA/EP), AND ASSUME THAT THE M/MO/R APPROVAL OBVIATES REGIONAL NEED FOR REGIONAL CLEARANCE.
THE EMBASSY IS ALREADY REPORTING NEARLY ALL THE REQUESTED DATA SEMI-ANNUALLY IN THE ECONOMIC TRENDS REPORT,AND SUBMITTING AS WELL ALL OF THE STATISTICAL DATA REQUESTED IN REF
A AS IT BECOMES AVAILABLE AS PART OF THE CERP PUBLICATIONS PROGRAM (WHETHER WEEKLY, MONTHLY OR QUARTERLY).
IS THE NEW REQUIREMENT OF SUCH HIGH PRIORITY THAT DUPLICATION BECOMES ESSENTIAL?

(C) WOULD INTERESTED END USERS FIND IT SATISFACTORY FOR THE POST TO SUBMIT A BRIEF SUMMARY OF ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENTS FOR THE MONTH, CITING ONLY THOSE STATISTICS RELEVANT TO SPECIFIC MONTHLY KEY ISSUES?

ANSWERS TO THE POINTS RAISED WILL BE HELPFUL TO THE EMBASSY IN ADJUSTING ITS VOLUNTARY REPORTING PLANS IN ORDER TO ALLOW FOR THIS NEW REQUIREMENT.

THE SWEDISH DELEGATION TO THE INTER-AMERICAN DEVELOPMENT BANK ANNUAL MEETING IN VANCOUVER, APRIL 17-19, WILL BE LED BY JOHAN NORDENFALK, UNDER SECRETARY OF THE MINISTRY OF COMMERCE, AND WILL INCLUDE, FROM STOCKHOLM, CAROLINE FLEETWOOD OF THE MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS AND BJORN SKALA OF THE MINISTRY FOR INTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT COOPERATION, AND, FROM WASH- INGTON, ULF DINKELSPIEL OF THE SWEDISH EMBASSY.

ALSO, THE SWEDISH DELEGATION WILL INCLUDE KARL WARNBERG, HEAD OF THE SWEDISH EXPORT COUNCIL, AMBASSADOR GORAN ENGBLOM, SWEDISH AMBASSADOR TO PERU, AND REPRESENTATIVES OF THE SWEDISH INDUS- TRIAL FEDERATION, THE SWEDISH BUILDING CONTRACTORS, SWEDISH BANKERS ASSOCIATION, AND PROBABLY OTHERS.
(SOME OF THESE PERSONAGES WILL BE IN SAN FRANCISCO BEFORE THE VANCOUVER MEETING, FOR A "SEMINAR ON ALASKA", ORGANIZED BY THE SWEDISH CONSULATE GENERAL.
THEY PROCEED TO VANCOUVER ON SATURDAY, APRIL 15.) 2.
NORDENFALK WOULD LIKE TO MEET WITH ASSISTANT SECRETARY BERGSTEN TO DISCUSS (1) HUMAN RIGHTS CONSIDERATIONS IN THE IDB; (2) PROTECTIONISM; (3) TRANSFER OF TECHNOLOGY.
COMMENT: THE PARTICIPATION OF REPRESENTATIVES FROM INDUS- TRY, BANKING, ETC., ILLUSTRATES SWEDEN'S INTEREST IN DEVELOP- ING TRADE AND INVESTMENT THROUGH ITS NEW MEMBERSHIP IN THE IDB.

THE FACT THAT THE MINISTRY OF COMMERCE FUNDED SWEDEN'S IDB MEMBERSHIP, RATHER THAN THE DEVELOPMENT COOPERATION MINISTRY, HAS PERMITTED THE GOS TO ACCENTUATE TRADE--AND EMPLOYMENT IN SWEDEN--THROUGH THE IDB, I.E., THROUGH CONTRACTS WHICH THE IDB MIGHT FUND.
AMBASSADOR ENGBLOM PREPARED A SPECIAL SUTDY IN 1977 ON INTEGRATING SWEDISH INDUSTRIES MORE CLOSELY WITH SWEDISH FOREIGN AID AND HE CAN BE EXPECTED TO BE AN ACTIVE MEMBER OF THE SWEDISH TEAM.
KENNEDY-MINOTT ']

['FOLLOWING IS TEXT OF SATURDAY'S EVENING READING: 1.
KOREAN PRISONER RELEASE.

THE KOREAN GOVERNMENT HAS ANNOUNCED THE RELEASE TODAY OF ALL BUT ONE OF THE "MYONGDONG PRISONERS," THE OPPOSITION POLITICAL AND RELIGIOUS FIGURES ARRESTED IN CONNECTION WITH THE ISSUANCE OF ANTI-GOVERNMENT MANIFESTO AT MYONGDONG CATHEDRAL IN SEOUL IN 1976.
FORMER PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE KIM DAE-JUNG, THE MOST PROMINENT OF THE PRISONERS, WAS NOT RELEASED, BUT HAS BEEN MOVED TO SEOUL UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL FOR MEDICAL TREATMENT.
WE HAVE ISSUED A STATEMENT TO THE PRESS WELCOMING RECENT RELEASES OF POLITICAL PRISONERS BY INDONESIA, PAKISTAN, AND BANGLADESH.
RIBICOFF ANTI-TERRORISM BILL.
FOLLOWING THE SCC MEETING LAST TUESDAY, THE HEAD OF OUR ANTI-TERRORISM WORKING GROUP MET WITH STAFFERS FOR RIBICOFF AND JAVITS TO DISCUSS INFORMALLY OUR COMMENTS ON THE RIBICOFF BILL.

THE STAFFERS INDICATED AN ENCOURAGING WILLINGNESS TO AMEND TROUBLESOME AREAS OF THE BILL; FOR EXAMPLE: (A) THEY WOULD CONSIDER GIVING STATUTORY EFFECT TO THE PRESENT ORGANIZATIONAL ARRANGEMENTS UNDER THE SCC; (B) THEY ARE INCLINED TO DROP THE ONE-HOUSE VETO FEATURE; (C) AND THEY DO NOT INSIST ON AUTOMATIC SANCTIONS, BUT WILL PRESS FOR AN INDICATION OF ADMINISTRATION RESOLVE TO ACT AGAINST COUNTRIES WHICH SUPPORT INTERNATIONAL TERRORISM OR HAVE INADEQUATE AIRPORT SECURITY (THE FAILURE TO INVOKE THE AUTHORITY UNDER THE 1974 ANTI-HIJACKING ACT WAS A FREQUENT THEME).

THE STAFFERS INDICATED THAT IT WOULD NOT BE POSSIBLE TO REDRAFT THE BILL BEFORE THE HEARINGS START JANUARY 23 BECAUSE OF THE HEAVY TRAVEL SCHEDULES OF SENATORS RIBICOFF AND JAVITS IN JANUARY, CONCURRENT STAFF TRAVEL RELATED TO THE BILL, AND THE DESIRE TO HEAR ALL SCHEDULED WITNESSES BEFORE BEGINNING THE MARK-UP.

UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES, RIBICOFF HAS SUGGESTED THE SECRETARY ENDORSE THE THRUST OF THE BILL, STRESS THE IMPORTANCE OF IMPROVING OUR METHODS FOR DEALING WITH TERRORISM, AND NOTE THAT THE BILL NEEDS SOME ADJUSTMENTS.

I HAVE ASKED THAT CY'S TESTIMONY BE DRAFTED ON A POSITIVE AND AFFIRMATIVE BASIS, WITHOUT ANY LONG RECITAL OF OUR RESERVATIONS BUT WITH AN INDICATION THAT OUR STAFFS ARE WORKING HARMONIOUSLY ON SPECIFIC ADJUSTMENTS. 3.
CAMBODIA-VIETNAM BREAK.

CAMBODIA HAS "TEMPORARILY" BROKEN RELATIONS WITH VIETNAM AND ACCUSED VIETNAM OF AGGRESSION IN AN INTEMPERATE COMMUNIQUE COMPARING VIETNAMESE ATTACKS INTO EASTERN CAMBODIA WITH HITLER'S THRUST INTO CZECHOSLOVAKIA.
THIS IS THE FIRST SIGNIFICANT PUBLIC REACTION TO INTENSIFIED THOUGH INTERMITTENT FIGHTING WHICH BEGAN LAST SPRING.
THE FIGHTING HAS BEEN HEAVY IN RECENT WEEKS AS VIETNAM TROOPS IN DIVISION STRENGTH MOVED 10-15 KM. INTO CAMBODIA.

THE CAUSES FOR THE FIGHTING INCLUDE CAMBODIA'S VIEW THAT THE VIETNAMESE (AND SOVIETS) ARE TRYING TO PRESSURE THEM INTO AN INDOCHINA FEDERATION UNDER VIETNAMESE DOMINATION, AND VIETNAM'S VIEW THAT CAMBODIA, WITH CHINESE SUPPORT, HAS MADE UNREASONABLE TERRITORIAL CLAIMS.
CENTURIES OF ANIMOSITY FUEL THIS DISPUTE.
PUBLIC DISCLOSURE OF THE CAMBODIA/VIETNAM FIGHTING MAY HAVE SIGNIFICANT EFFECTS
WELL BEYOND INDOCHINA.
CHINA, WHICH HAD EARLIER IMPLIED PUBLIC SUPPORT FOR CAMBODIA'S DEFENSIVE EFFORTS, HAS REPORTEDLY DEPLORED THE BORDER CLASHES AND SUGGESTED RESOLUTION BY PEACEFUL NEGOTIATIONS.
CHINA'S GREATER INTEREST IS IN REGIONAL STABILITY.
THE CAMBODIANS HAVE CHARGED THAT SOME "FOREIGNERS" COMMAND VIETNAMESE UNITS IN THE ATTACKING FORCES, A PROBABLE REFERENCE TO SOVIETS, BUT WE HAVE NO EVIDENCE OF SUCH THIRD-COUNTRY INVOLVEMENT.
MEANWHILE, REPORTS OF THE GRUESOME SLAUGHTER OF THE MIDDLE AND UPPER CLASSES IN CAMBODIA MOUNT.
CHRISTOPHER ']

MFA HAS CALLED TO OUR ATTENTION AN AIR BROADCAST OF MAY 30 WHICH REPORTED THAT FORMER AZAD KASHMIR PRESIDENT ABDUL QAYYUM KHAN HAS SAID IN A LETTER TO SHEIKH ABDULLAH THAT THE PEOPLE OF AK ARE LIVING IN PERPETUAL TERROR AND DO NOT WANT TO REMAIN WITHIN PAKISTAN.
THE AIR ACCOUNT IS SAID TO HAVE REPORTED THAT THE LETTER WAS PUBLISHED IN THE SRINIGAR WEEKLY AAINA.
AS YOU WILL RECALL, GOP STACKED CARDS AGAINST QAYYUM IN LAST MONTH'S AK RACE AND HE FINALLY BOYCOTTED ELECTION (ISLAMABAD 4617).
HE REPORTEDLY CHARGED DURING COURSE OF CAMPAIGN THAT IF GOP PERSISTED IN GROSS INTERFERENCE IN ELECTION AZAD KASHMIRIS WOULD FLEE ACROSS BORDER TO INDIAN KASHMIR.
WE WOULD APPRECIATE ANYTHING YOU CAN SEND US ON THIS STORY, INCLUDING IF AT ALL POSSIBLE TEXT OF ALLEGED QAYYUM-ABDULLAH LETTER AS REPORTEDLY PUBLISHED IN AAINA.
BYROADE "]

JAPANESE COLOR TV MAKERS REACTED WITH EMOTIONALISM TO ITC RECOMMENDATIONS, ALL CLAIMING THAT ITC DECISION FOR TARIFF HIKE IS MORE SEVERE THAN NUMERICAL QUOTA RESTRICTIONS.

ALL KINDS OF FIGURES ARE FLYING ABOUT, WITH SOME COMPANIES CLAIMING JAPANESE COLOR TV EXPORTS TO U.S. WILL DROP TO LESS THAN ONE MILLION SETS PER YEAR IF ITC RECOMMENDATIONS ARE IMPLEMENTED, AND PRICES OF SETS IN U.S. WILL INCREASE AS MUCH AS 40 PERCENT.
FOLOWING INITIAL EXPRESSIONS OF OUTRAGE, JAPANESE BUSINESSMEN HAVE RETIRED TO THEIR CALCULATORS TO DETEMINE ACTUAL IMPACT ON THEIR OWN COMPANIES.
BIGGEST OUTBURSTS,AS EXPECTED, CAME FROM MAJOR EXPORTERS -- SANYO, SHARP, AND TOSHIBA -- WHO REPORTEDLY ACCOUNT
FOOR
60PERCENT OF EXPORTS TO U.S. OTHER MANUFACTURERS SUCH AS SONY,VICTOR,AND MITSUBISHI ELECTRIC, WERE DISTURBED BY ITC'S OPTING FOR TARIFF HIKE.

THESE COMPANIES STATE THEY ARE ALREADY SELLING IN U.S. AT PRICES EQUAL TO OR HIGHER THAN U.S. SETS, AND TARIFF HIKE WOULD PENALIZE THEM MORE THAN THE LOWER-PRICED "OFFENDERS" SUCH AS SANYO AND TOSHIBA. 3.
JAPANESE MAKERS ALL CLAIM THEY WILL LOSE PRICE COMPETITIVENESS IN U.S. MARKET AND THAT CONSUMERS AND MASS RETAILERS WILL SWITCH TO U.S.-MADE SETS.

JAPAN PURCHASING MANAGER FOR MAJOR U.S. MASS RETAILER WAS NOT THIS PESSIMISTIC, HOWEVER, HE TOLD EMBOFF THAT ACTUAL IMPACT OF ITC TARRIF HIKE WILL DEPEND UPON U.S. DEMAND FOR COLOR TV'S AND CONSUMER PREFERENCES.
HE ADDED, "IF JAPANESE MANUFACTURERS' ARGUMENTS ABOUT THEIR QUALITY, COMPETENCE IN SMALL SCREEN SETS, AND PRODUCTION EFFICIENCY ARE REALLY TRUE, THEN THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE TO WORRY TOO MUCH." 4.
TOKYO STOCK MARKET TOOK ITC DECISION IN STRIDE, WITH ONLY SONY CLOSING LOWER.

FOLLOWING IS TEXT OF PRESS COVERAGE
IN MAY 6 EDITION OF NEW YORK TIMES.
PAGE 24 ARTICLE BY DAVID BURNHAM, FRIDAY MAY 5: BEGIN QUOTE:

A STATE DEPARTMENT OFFICIAL TESTIFIED IN AN ESPIONAGE TRIAL TODAY THAT A SERIES OF GOVERNMENT MESSAGES ALLEGEDLY TRANSMITTED TO VIETNAM COULD AFFECT FOREIGN RELATIONS AND THE NATIONAL DEFENSE OF THE UNITED STATES.
UNDER CROSS-EXAMINATION, HOWEVER, THE OFFICIAL ACKNOWLEDGED THAT A YEAR AGO HE TOLD A STATE DEPARTMENT SECURITY EXPERT THAT THE COMPROMISING OF THE DOCUMENTS WOULD RESULT IN "MINOR OR NO DAMAGE."
THE OFFICIAL WHO APPEARED TO HAVE CHANGED HIS OPINION WAS KENNETH M. QUINN, NOW A SPECIAL ASSISTANT TO RICHARD HOLBROOKE, THE ASSISTANT SECRETARY OF STATE FOR EAST ASIAN AND PACIFIC AFFIARS.
entities: ASSISTANT SECRETARY OF STATE FOR EAST ASIAN AND PACIFIC AFFIARS

content: MR. QUINN HAD BEEN CALLED BY FEDERAL PROSECUTORS TO TELL THE JURY IN FEDERAL COURT HERE OF THE IMPORTANCE OF THE DOCUMENTS THAT DAVID TRUONG, A 32-YEAR-OLD VIETNAMESE GRADUATE STUDENT, AND RONALD L. HUMPHREY, 42, AN OFFICIAL IN THE UNITED STATES INFORMATION AGENCY, HAVE BEEN ACCUSED OF STEALING AND TRANSMITTING TO MEMBERS OF THE COMMUNIST GOVERNMENT OF VIETNAM.
BOTH HAVE DENIED THE ESPIONAGE AND OTHER CHARGES BROUGHT AGAINST THEM.
NEW MOTION TO DISMISS.

IN A SECOND DEVELOPMENT TODAY, LAWYERS FOR MR. TRUONG MADE A SUPPLEMENTAL MOTION TO DISMISS THE INDICTMENTS AGAINST HIM BECAUSE OF THE DIS- COVERY LAST NIGHT OF AN ANALYSIS BY THE CENTRAL INTELLIGENCE AGENCY SAYING THAT THE DECISION TO PROSECUTE THE TWO MEN "COULD BE A VERY CLOSE CALL."

THE PREVIOUSLY CLASSIFIED STUDY, DATED MARCH 13, SAID THAT THE CASE WOULD BE DIFFICULT TO PRESENT TO A JURY BUT THAT "A NUMBER OF INDIVIDUAL CABLES COULD BE SAID AT LEAST TANGENTIALLY TO 'RELATE TO THE NATIONAL DEFENSE' BY A JESUIT."
THE JESUITS, OR MEMBERS OF THE SOCIETY OF JESUS, A CATHOLIC RELIGIOUS ORDER, ARE WIDELY KNOWN FOR THE METICULOUS AND DETERMINED ARGUMENTS THEY MAKE IN DEFENSE OF THEIR BELIEFS.
THE C.I.A. STUDY WAS WRITTEN BY RICHARD LEHMAN, AN OFFICIAL IN THE NATIONAL FOREIGN ASSESSMENT CENTER.

HE SAID THAT PERHAPS "THE MOST RESPECTABLE ARGUMENT" FOR WHY THE DOCU- MENTS COULD BE SAID TO AFFECT NATIONAL DEFENSE IS THAT THEY DEALT WITH VIETNAM, STILL CONSIDERED AN ENEMY STATE, AND "IN THEIR TOTALITY WOULD INDEED GIVE THE VIETNAMESE GOVERNMENT INSIGHTS"
INTO EFFORTS BY THE UNITED STATES TO NEGOTIATE A SETTLEMENT.
JUDGE DID NOT RULE.
FEDERAL DISTRICT JUDGE ALBERT V. BRYAN, JR.
entities: FEDERAL DISTRICT JUDGE ALBERT V. BRYAN, JR.

content: DID NOT RULE ON THE MOTION TO DISMISS THE INDICTMENT AGAINST MR. TRUONG.
THE QUESTION OF WHETHER THE DOCUMENTS THAT THE GOVERNMENT HAS CHARGED WERE TRANSMITTED TO VIETNAM ARE RELATED TO THE NATIONAL DEFENSE IS CRITICAL TO BOTH SIDES.
IF THE JURY DECIDES THAT THEY ARE OF LESSER IMPORTANCE, THIS WOULD MEAN THE TWO DEFENDANTS COULD NOT BE CONVICTED OF ESPIONAGE, THE MOST SERIOUS CHARGE BROUGHT AGAINST THEM.
THEY ALSO HAVE BEEN CHARGED WITH CONSPIRACY AND FAILURE TO REGISTER AS FOREIGN AGENTS.
IN TODAY'S SESSION, MR. QUINN PROVIDED A DETAILED ANALYSIS TO THE JURY OF HOW THE DOCUMENTS, IN HIS OPINION, WOULD AFFECT THE FOREIGN POLICY OF THE UNITED STATES AND THUS ITS NATIONAL DEFENSE.
BUT IN CROSS-EXAMINATION, HE ACKNOWLEDGED THAT ON MAY 11, 1977, HE SAID "SOMETHING TO THE EFFECT" THAT THE CABLES WOULD RESULT IN "MINOR OR NO DAMAGE."
HE DID NOT EXPLAIN THE REASONS FOR THE CHANGE IN HIS POSITION.
A REPORT BY ANOTHER OFFICIAL IN THE STATE DEPARTMENT OFFICE OF EAST ASIAN AFFAIRS ALSO WAS QUOTED YESTERDAY.
entities: STATE DEPARTMENT OFFICE OF EAST ASIAN AFFAIRS

content: IT CONCLUDED THAT THERE WAS "LITTLE OF SENSITIVE NATURE IN THE DOCUMENTS" AND THE DAMAGE OF THEIR FALLING INTO VIETNAM'S HANDS HAD BEEN LIGHT."
END TEXT.

TWO FURTHER CONTRASTING NOTES ON SYG WALDHEIM'S PROSPECTS FOR REAPPOINTMENT REFLECT ACTIVITY IN RUMOR MILL
WITHIN LAST FEW DAYS.
SECRETARIAT SOURCES REPORT THAT PRC PERM REP HUANG HUA HAS INFORMED UNGA PRESIDENT AMER- ASINGHE
THAT IN CHINESE VIEW HOLDING ELECTION FOR SYG BEFORE DECEMBER WOULD BE QUOTE UNDIGNIFIED HASTE UNQUOTE.

ON A DIFFERENT LINE, HOWEVER, DURING EC-9 LUNCHEON FOR GOVERNOR SCRANTON OCTOBER 14, FRG PERM REP VON WECHMAR TOLD POLCOUNS THAT LATE OCTOBER 13 WALDHEIM HAD APPROACHED HIM PRIVATELY DURING A SOCIAL FUNCTION AND EXPRESSED A DESIRE TO MOVE SOON TOWARD FORMAL ACTION IN SECURITY COUNCIL -- IN LIGHT OF OVERWHELMING SUPPORT SYG HAD RECEIVED FROM MANY QUARTERS.
HE SUGGESTED TO VON WECHMAR THAT, IF AGREEABLE, HE MIGHT APPROACH UNSC PRESIDENT AKHUND ON HIS OWN ACCOUNT -- WITHOUT REFERENCE TO ANY CONVERSATION WITH WALDHEIM -- TO URGE EARLY ACTION IN SC.
VON WECHMAR SAID HE PROBABLY WOULD CHECK WITH AKHUND, BUT HE HAD NO CONFIDENCE THAT THIS KIND OF ACTION WOULD INFLUENCE TIMING OF SC DEBATE.
HE REFERRED TO RUMORS OF A DELAY IN PROCESS, WHICH HE ALSO HAD PICKED UP FROM SEVERAL SOURCES.

SENATOR PERCY SPENT AFTERNOON
AND
EVENING JANUARY 11 IN BAHRAIN.
IT WAS HIGHEST-
POWERED VISIT WE HAVE HAD SINCE I ARRIVED IN JUNE.
IT GAVE EVERY INDICATION OF HAVING A NEARLY PERFECT IMPACT.
SENATOR HAD ONE HOUR MEETING WITH AMIR, WITH PRIME MINISTER ATTENDING LATTER HALF.
(AT SENATOR'S REQUEST SEPTEL WILL SUMMARIZE DISCUSSION)
HE TALKED UP, NOT DOWN, TO THEM, MADE SOME EXCELLENT POINTS AND DREW THEM OUT IMPRESSIVELY.
(AMIR AT ONE POINT WHISPERED TO ME NERVOUSLY
"I HOPE I AM SAYING THE RIGHT THINGS.").

THEY WERE OBVIOUSLY AWARE THEY WERE DEALING WITH A POWERFUL AND IMPRESSIVE AMERICAN POLITICAL FIGURE AND WERE CLEARLY DELIGHTED WITH HIS RECEPTIVENESS TO THEIR CONCERNS AND HIS OWN CONCERN FOR PEACE AND INTERNATIONAL COOPERATION.
LATER AT RESIDENCE DINNER FOREIGN MINISTER GOT IN GOOD HOUR OF WIDE-RANGING EXCHANGE WITH SENATOR AND CAME AWAY EFFUSIVELY IMPRESSED.
SENATOR HELD ONE HOUR DISCUSSION WITH REPRESENTATIVES AMERICAN BUSINESS COMMUNITY.
THEY WERE GRATEFUL FOR CHANCE TO AIR THEIR VIEWS ON HOW U.S. MIDDLE EAST POLICY AFFECTS THEIR INTERESTS.
SENATOR SEEMED IMPRESSED BY THEIR UNANIMITY OF ENTHUSIASM FOR BAHRAIN AS HOSPITABLE NATURAL SITE FOR CON- DUCTING REGIONAL SERVICE OPERATIONS.
COMMENT: SHORTLY AFTER I ARRIVED, AMIR URGED ME TO PRODUCE SOME VISITORS "FROM U.S. SENATE, ESPECIALLY FOREIGN RELATIONS COMMITTEE."
PERCY VISIT WAS IDEAL RESPONSE, PARTICULARLY WELCOME AT
A RELATIVELY CRITICAL TIME IN OUR RELATIONS.
FROM PERSPECTIVE WASHINGTON OR LARGER CAPITALS IT IS DIFFICULT TO VIZUALIZE HOW MUCH IMPACT A VISIT OF THIS TYPE
HAS IN NOT JUST SYMBOLIZING BUT ACTUALLY ADDING SUBSTANCE TO EXPANSION US/BAHRAIN RELATIONS.

(FOR FUTURE REFERENCE GOB WOULD HAVE PREFERRED A SOMEWHAT LONGER STOP, AND WE MUST BE CAREFUL NOT TO OVER BURDEN BAHRAINIS WITH SUCH VISITS) FROM THE PERSPECTIVE OF THIS LITTLE SPOT SENATOR PERCY'S CALL HERE WAS A SMASHING SUCCESS, FOR WHICH GOB (AND I) MOST GRATEFUL.
TWINAM ']
